Canadian Butter Tarts
  --Overwatch cookbook

Crust:
1/2 c unsalted butter
1 c ap flour
2 tbsp packed dark brown sugar
1/4 c rolled oats

Butter and lightly flour 8" square baking pan and preheat oven to 350F. Rub the butter into the flour, sugar, and oats for the crust until you ha a nice, soft. and crumbly mixture. Press this into the bottom of the prepared pan, and bake for 5 min. Remove from oven and set aside.

1/2 c walnuts
1/2 c unsalted butter, softened
2 eggs
1 c packed dark brown sugar
2 tbsp maple syrup
1/2 tsp vanilla
1/4 tsp salt
1/2 tsp baking powder
powdered sugar for dusting (optional)

Pulse walnuts in a food processor to a fine consistency. In a medium mixing bowl, stir together all the ingredients (except powdered sugar), and pour over the crust. Bake for 20 min. Allow to cool slightly before cuttinr into squares with a buttered knife. Dust with powdered sugar if you like. Serve.
